Digital Literacy Course Task:
While researching digital literacy and online practices, what surprised me the most was how common cyber risks are and how easily people fall into traps like phishing emails or weak password usage.
I realized that even small mistakes, such as clicking unknown links or sharing personal information casually, can lead to serious consequences.
I also learned that many students are not fully aware of professional communication standards and online safety measures.
As a result of this learning, one habit I will personally change is improving my password security by using strong, unique passwords for different accounts and enabling two-factor authentication wherever possible.
I will also be more careful while checking emails and avoid clicking suspicious links.
Overall, this experience has made me more responsible and aware while using digital platforms.
